          "body": {
            "text": "There are a few established routes offering some unusual climbing. There is also potential for a few more routes on the walls around the main crag. The crag lies in beautiful deciduous woodland, with an archery range in front of the main crag.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Park behind Kortedala fire station and walk downhill for about 400 metres until you see the crag on the right-hand side of the road. By public transport, take the tram and get off at Kortedala torg. Follow Tideräkningsgatan towards Angered until you see the fire station, then continue past it for about 400 metres until you see the crag on the right-hand side of the road. Total walking distance about 1 km.\n\nTo reach Burmaklippan and the crags south of it, either follow the power line from the allotments or make your way down to them along the paths from the fire station or Dagjämingsgatan. Do not park by the allotments.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "oversikt": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Overview",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vanstra-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Left Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "No routes have been developed on this wall, which is about 10 metres high.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bagskyttevaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Archery Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The wall behind the archery ranges. The crag is about 15–18 metres high and roughly 100 metres wide. The Göteborg guidebook provides good directions, and the routes are easy to find.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hogra-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Right Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The first small wall you see when approaching from Tideräkningsgatan. Perhaps it should be called Tidräkningsväggen? About 10 metres high. There is potential for more routes and boulder problems. Watch out for angry ants.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "burmaklippan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Burmaklippan",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Park by the fire station, walk down to the allotments and follow the power lines. Do not park in the allotment area. Alternatively, walk through the woods from Dagjämningsgatan.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "linjelusta-klippan": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Linjelusta-klippan",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "tardis-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "TARDIS Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Continue another 100 metres south and another wall appears, the same height and angle as the others but wider. The easiest approach is from Dagjämningsgatan.\n\nFollow the path from Dagjämningsgatan downhill until you reach a rusty fence. The following routes are located there:",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kalendervagen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Kalendervägen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "There are three trad routes at Kalendervägen 38 in Kortedala. They are marked T1, T2 and T3 on a topo on Gbg Bouldering Online, together with a number of boulder problems. See Kortedala > Kalendervägen on GBO (http://gbo.crimp.se/omraden.php?oid=13&sid=47).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "kortedala-led-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Near the far left of the main wall, you will see two unusual holes. The route climbs between them to a ledge, then continues to the top.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kortedala-led-2": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts directly below the right-hand end of the ledge on Hole in the wall and climbs straight up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kortedala-led-4": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts by a tree.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kortedala-led-6": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climbs through the crack splitting the roof.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kortedala-led-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A mini-chimney or wide crack.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kortedala-led-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climb through a cave to a corner with a fine crack. Follow this past a small roof and onto the face. Then cross Time vortex and climb straight up via ledges.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kortedala"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
